{
  "stem": "26699.2",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They were [PAUSES] extremists.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But the general population was mild with us.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] Generally we could survive there.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we survived.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I couldn't complain that we suffered after the pogrom as people suffered in other countries.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We still had enough food, and my grandmother was a fantastic cook, was cooking for the whole family, and was preparing for the winter with all the jams and preserved fruit and vegetables, pickles and everything, and growing chicken and the geese.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And it was a reasonable life.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "From this point of view, I can say that the Romanian population wasn't bad to the Jews in general, with the exception of the Iron Guard.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, but actually I read in some publications that something really awkward happened, that the local Jewish community managed to bribe the Iron Guard, which is typical for the Romanian mentality, to be corrupt.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But to such an extent that an organization like the Iron Guard to be bribed by the Jews, that show quite a lot.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 7 SECONDS] I was spending most of my time with [PAUSES] [CLEARS THROAT] school.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "My mother-- my mother's ambition was to become a pianist, which didn't occur, because I didn't have the talent.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But she insisted a lot.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We had a piano.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "She was playing piano and was educated by her family as a good Jewish girl that she must play piano and speak foreign languages, which actually helped us with translation she gave me from German-- from the German hero.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And [LAUGHS] we had a piano, so I had to practice and play.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So I did it.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
